00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:22,000
 And I said to Sonny, "I will try."

487
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:24,000
 And you know what he says to me?

488
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,000
 "I don't care if you try.

489
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:30,000
 I didn't hire you to try.

490
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:32,000
 I hired you to get this job done.

491
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:35,000
 Now, if you can't get this done, I will fire you right now and

492
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 replace you with someone who can.

493
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,000
 Can you get the job done?"

494
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 I says, "I will."

495
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 And he unmutes me and says, "We'll get the job done."

496
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:46,000
 He walks out of there and says, "Always remember, don't try

497
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:47,000
 hard.

498
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 Get the job done."

499
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:50,000
 And he walks out.

500
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:54,000
 A year later, and this is the biggest lesson I learned, and it

501
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:56,000
 ties in with everything that we're talking about a year

502
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,000
 later.

503
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:02,000
 Sonny comes in, and we have an employee gathering, and he says,

504
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:05,000
 "This year's Employee of the Year is Tommy Lee."

505
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:08,000
 And he says, "Tommy Lee, wherever I go, in all of the

506
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,000
 travels, and all the -- when I talk with clients like AT&T,

507
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:15,000
 Sprint, and Verizon, they all say, 'If Tommy Lee's on the job,

508
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,000
 we'll hire you and give you the business.'

509
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:20,000
 All of the sales development, all of our -- and when I talk

510
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:23,000
 with the janitors, they all know who this guy is.

511
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:27,000
 And then I talk with him, and all of us go out to the bars on

512
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 Fridays, but this guy goes to his church and works with his

513
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,000
 youth.

514
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,000
 That's why I hear him.

515
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 And he says to this, he says, "I don't follow Jesus, but if this

516
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:42,000
 is what it means to follow Jesus, then sign me up."

517
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 And he says that.

518
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:48,000
 And you know what happened after that?

519
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:53,000
 I had a girl who comes over to me, and she was my admin.

520
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 And she says, "Tommy, how are you so joyful?

521
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:00,000
 I've had three miscarriages.

522
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:04,000
 How do you see God in the midst of all these things?"

523
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 I had another guy, his name was Patrick.

524
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,000
 Patrick would go out to the bars all the time.

525
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:11,000
 Patrick was always getting drunk.

526
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:15,000
 And he says to me, "Tommy, what keeps you going?

527
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 What's your purpose in life?

528
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 Because I haven't found it yet."

529
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 My boss, Dan, who promoted me as project manager, calls me up one

530
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 day and says, "Tommy, I need you to stay after work.

531
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:29,000
 I need to talk with you about something."

532
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 I walk in after work, and he says, "Hey, Tommy, my daughter

533
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,000
 has been diagnosed with a heart issue.

534
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,000
 Can you pray for me?

535
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:39,000
 Can we spend some time praying?"

536
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 And during Christmas, I would give their names,

537
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 give them all Bibles.

538
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,000
 And that was what I did for Christmas, and I would put their

539
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 name on it and gave it to each one of them.

540
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:51,000
 And during my cancer journey when I was gone,

541
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:53,000
 I got these Facebook messages.

542
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:56,000
 And this is now 10 years later.

543
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,000
 And I get these Facebook messages.

544
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,000
 One of them was from Erin, the girl who had three miscarriages,

545
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 and says to me, "Tommy, I have three beautiful daughters now.

546
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:08,000
 I lead the VBS in their church.

547
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 I came to know the Lord, and I read your Bible.

548
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 Your Bible's still with me."

549
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,000
 The other guy, Patrick, Patrick says to me, "Tommy, I'm still,

550
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:20,000
 like, going out all the time and drinking, but I got married.

551
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:23,000
 But I did start going to church, and your Bible's the one that I

552
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:26,000
 bring to church every single day."

553
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 Dan, these are all 10 years later, his wife calls me up

554
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:35,000
 and says to me, "I saw on Facebook that you were

555
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,000
 struggling with cancer.

556
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:42,000
 Your former boss, Dan, is also struggling with cancer.

557
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:46,000
 Can you call him because your Bible is still sitting right

558
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:49,000
 there by his bedside?"

559
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:52,000
 You never know how God uses you.

560
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:56,000
 You never know what God is calling you to do,

561
00:32:56,000 --> 00:33:01,000
 all because you do your job well.

562
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:07,000
 And you are faithful to wherever God has called you to be.

563
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:10,000
 Whether it's a job that you can't stand,

564
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 whether it's a job that you hate,

565
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 whether it's a job where you just don't like the industry,

566
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:19,000
 where you don't like your characters, all of those things,

567
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 are you faithful to where God has placed you at?

568
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 And are you always praying and asking,

569
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 "What is that vision that you have for me?

570
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 What are you preparing me to do?"

571
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 For Gideon, he leads him on this journey.

572
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 This guy who is at the weakest of all of the clans,

573
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:42,000
 that he is the weakest, he is the lowest of all the clans,

574
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 God is preparing him to be the leader of--

575
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 to fight against the minions.

576
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:51,000
 He is going to be their victor.

577
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:54,000
 What is God preparing you to be?

578
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:57,000
 And how is God using all the things that you're doing right

579
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:03,000
 now in your job to prepare you for what you're doing right now?

580
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:05,000
 Because you don't know.

581
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,000
 He may call you now.

582
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:10,000
 He may be calling you 10 years from now,

583
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,000
 do something unique or--

584
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:15,000
 what he's calling you to do is be faithful.

585
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 If you look at Nehemiah, he didn't call him until the late

586
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:23,000
 '70s, but he was faithful as compared to the king.

587
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:25,000
 And when it was time to rebuild the walls,

588
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,000
 do you know what the king did?

589
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:31,000
 His boss, the king, gave him time off,

590
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,000
 gave him all the money that he need,

591
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 gave him all the papers that he need to get all of those

592
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 different things, and gave him all the resources and materials.

593
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,000
 Why?

594
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 Because he liked Nehemiah and he had nothing better to do?

595
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,000
 No.

596
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 He was faithful as compared to the king.

597
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 Do your job well.

598
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 Be faithful day in and day out in your job.

599
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:02,000
 Make such a difference and impact in your job that you leave

600
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:08,000
 a lasting impact on the lives of people around you,

601
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:10,000
 that when you walk away from that job,

602
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 they're going to sit there and say, "Wow, look at that person.

603
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 I'm able to see Jesus through that person."

604
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,000
 That's what it means to be a Christ follower.

605
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:26,000
 That means you treat the janitors well.

606
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,000
 That means you treat the admins well.

607
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:30,000
 That means you treat your boss well.

608
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:35,000
 That means that every single person you treat well,

609
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:39,000
 that you do a good job, that you are productive,

610
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:42,000
 that because God has put me in that situation,

611
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 I will honor my boss by doing my work with such excellence.

612
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:51,000
 It glorifies God in all that we do.

613
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:54,000
 And during that time, you are always praying,

614
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:58,000
 "Lord, what is that vision that you have given me?

615
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:01,000
 What are you calling me to do?"

616
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:04,000
 Because God may choose and show you different things

617
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:06,000
 that he wants you to do.

618
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:10,000
 That's so important about faith and work.

619
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 Sixty percent of our day is spent at work.

620
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:17,000
 God calls us to work.

621
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:20,000
 God calls us to flourish and redeem.

622
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:26,000
 God has given you skills and talents to change your city,

623
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:31,000
 to change your community, to change your work,

624
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:35,000
 to make this world a different place.

625
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:38,000
 What is God calling you to do?

626
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:41,000
 What is the picture and name that he has given you?

627
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,000
 For Gideon, it was "Mighty Warrior."

628
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:49,000
 But too often, our insecurities causes us to look past

629
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,000
 what God is calling us to do.

630
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:54,000
 And for Gideon, he had to get past that insecurity

631
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:56,000
 of being from the weakest clan

632
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:59,000
 and being the weakest in the weakest clan.

633
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:03,000
 What is God calling you to do?

634
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:05,000
 We are motivated by grace.

635
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 We are saved by grace.

636
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:12,000
 The cross causes us, motivates us to be where we are.

637
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:17,000
 Our job now is to take that grace that we have in our life

638
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:20,000
 and to make a difference in all that we do.

639
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:23,000
 In Christ we pray. Amen.

640
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 Father, thank you for how you continue to serve and use us,

641
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:32,000
 how you've created us to become the person you want us to be.

642
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:37,000
 And so, Lord, may you continue to paint that journey over to us

643
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:44,000
 and allow us to see what that name that you have given us is, Lord.

644
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:48,000
 What is that name you have given us?

645
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:55,000
 How have you uniquely designed us to flourish

646
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:59,000
 and change this world and redeem this world for you?

647
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:03,000
 I pray all of us will be in that journey to see you.

648
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:05,000
 In Christ we pray. Amen.

649
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:07,000
 Thank you. Thanks, Mark.

